        "option_b_result": "INCORRECT - While updating the stakeholder register is a good practice, it's a planning activity and not the immediate action for communicating an urgent change. One-on-one meetings might be necessary for some, but a structured approach to communication is needed for all relevant stakeholders, which might involve more than just one-on-ones.",
        "option_c_result": "INCORRECT - Discussing with the core team is important, but delaying the notification to external stakeholders, especially for a regulatory update with significant impact, can lead to compliance issues or loss of trust. The communication strategy needs to be developed and executed quickly for all relevant parties.",
        "option_d_result": "CORRECT - For a critical and impactful regulatory change, developing a specific communication plan update is the most appropriate action. This ensures a structured approach to disseminating information, considering who needs to know what, when, and how, facilitating understanding and appropriate actions across all relevant stakeholder groups. This proactive and planned approach ensures effective communication, which is a core output of Manage Communications.",
