        "concepts_to_understand": "The purpose and tools of the Develop Team process, particularly the role of recognition and rewards in motivating team members and improving individual performance. Understanding that this is a specific, listed tool within the PMBOK's guidance for team development.",
        "additional_notes": "This is an easy question designed to test a direct recall of the tools and techniques within the 'Develop Team' process. The scenario explicitly states that a recognition program was implemented and led to individual performance improvements. The PMBOK Guide clearly lists 'Recognition and Rewards' as a tool and technique for the Develop Team process, aimed at motivating team members and reinforcing positive performance. The other options, while related to team development, are not the direct and primary purpose or mechanism described by a 'recognition program'. The question aims to confirm that the candidate can link a common project management activity to its specific PMP process tool.",
        "difficulty_level": "easy"
