        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - In the 'Develop Team' process, especially with a newly formed team of diverse backgrounds, establishing clear ground rules, communication protocols, and a shared understanding of project objectives is fundamental. A kick-off meeting serves this purpose, laying the groundwork for effective collaboration, minimizing misunderstandings, and setting expectations for how the team will operate. This is critical for moving beyond the 'forming' stage.",
        "option_c_result": "INCORRECT - While assigning tasks is necessary, doing so without first establishing ground rules and communication protocols can lead to confusion, conflict, and inefficiency, especially with a new, diverse team. Maximizing immediate productivity without building a cohesive foundation often leads to long-term problems.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - An off-site social event can be beneficial for team building and fostering informal relationships, but it should not be the very first step. Before building camaraderie, the team needs to understand its purpose, roles, and how it will function. Essential operational frameworks like ground rules and communication protocols take precedence.",
        "process_group": "Executing",
        "knowledge_area": "Integration",
        "tool": "Team-building activities, Ground Rules",
